{% from 'macros/card.njk' import card_ %}

{% extends "layout.njk" %}
{% set activeIndex = 3 %}
{% set title = 'JK - Skills' %}
{% set metaDescription = 'Skills page of Jay Karon\'s portfolio website.' %}

{% block content %}
<div class="container-fluid mt-3">
  <div class="row d-flex justify-content-around mx-1">

    {% set programmingContent %}
    <div class="row justify-content-around">
      <div class="col-md-6">
        <ul class="skillsList">
          <li>
            <strong>Languages</strong> - <small>(in order of familiarity)</small>
            <ul>
              <li>Python - programming language of choice. With packages like Django and NumPy</li>
              <li>JavaScript (& TS) - with all the npm goodies</li>
              <li>Java, C - basic familiarity with these guys</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Databases</strong> - Designing and maintaining both PostgreSQL and Mongo DBs
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Web Tech</strong> - React, D3, Webpack... Remember when HTML was enough to make a website?
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-5">
        <ul class="skillsList">
          <li>
            <strong>AWS Services</strong> - S3, Lambda, SQS... Makes developing more convenient than one day shipping
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Unix</strong> - I have forsaken the desktop for the command line
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Docker</strong> - Stop installing things and start developing
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Git</strong> - No other way to write code. Check out my <a
              href="https://github.com/jaykaron">GitHub</a>!
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Computer Vision</strong> - The magic of CV: <code>function(image) => return math(image)</code> ðŸŽ‰
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="iconHolder mb-2">
    <i class="fa fa-code" aria-hidden="true"></i>
  </div>
  {% endset %}
  {{ card_('Programming', '', programmingContent, additionalClass='col-lg-10')}}
</div>

<div class="row d-flex justify-content-around mx-1">
  {% set lifeContent %}
  <ul class="skillsList">
    <li>
      <strong>Math</strong> - I happen to be pretty good at this and enjoy it too! (Award on <a
        href="../../../experience">experience</a> page)
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Fast Learner</strong> - The trick, the ability to effictively skim results on Google and Stack Overflow
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Hard Working</strong> - People sometimes ask if I'm a morning person or a night person. I reply "a
      person person"
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Good Communicator</strong> - I actually think I'm just a good listener,
      but often this is enough to pass as a good communicator
    </li>
  </ul>
  <div class="iconHolder">
    <i class="fa fa-wrench" aria-hidden="true"></i>
  </div>
  {% endset %}
  {{ card_('Life Skills', '', lifeContent, additionalClass='col-lg-5')}}


  {% set miscContent %}
  <ul class="skillsList">
    <li>
      <strong>Reading</strong> - Check out my <a href='/books'>book reviews</a>!
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Repairing things</strong> - My motto is: "if you want it done right, don't do it yourself", but
      that is not nearly as much fun
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Bookbinding</strong> - Unlike e-books, paper books still fall apart
    </li>
  </ul>
  <div class="iconHolder">
    <i class="fa fa-user-circle-o" aria-hidden="true"></i>
  </div>
